               <msContents>
                  <summary>Excerpts from the ritual for Passion Week, ግብረ፡ ሕማማት, Halleluiatic hymn to the Trinity, Story of the Trinity, Sword of the Trinity, ሰይፈ፡ ሥላሴ፡,  Image of the Trinity, መልክአ፡ ሥላሴ፡</summary>
                     <textLang mainLang="gez">Gə‘əz</textLang>

                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1"><locus from = "1r" to = "6v"/><title type = "complete" ref = "LIT1544Gebrah"/><note>Excerpts, with musical notation</note>
                    <incipit>
                      ሶበ፡ ሰቀልዎ፡ ሶበ፡ ሰቀልዎ፡ ሶበ፡ ሰቀልዎ፡ ለእግዚእነ፡ ፀሐይ፡ ጸልመ፡ ወወርኅ፡ ደመ፡ ኮነ፡...
                    </incipit>
                    </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2"><locus from = "7r" to = "8r"/>
                    <title>Halleluiatic hymn to the Trinity. (see <title ref = "EMIP00039"/>, f. 19r</title>
                    <incipit xml:lang = "gez">
                      አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ መላእክቲሁ፡ ለስሉስ። ሩጸሎሙ፡ ከመ፡ ነፋስ፡...
                    </incipit>
                    </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i3"><locus from = "9r" to = "12r"/><title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2286ZenaSellase"/></msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i4"><locus from = "12r" to = "48r"/><title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2296Sayfas"/>
                    <note>
                      The usual miracles are included. Incomplete; texts are erased to make room for the pictures. Arranged for the days of the week (
                      Monday, <locus target = "#12r"/>;
                      Tuesday, <locus target = "#17v"/>;
                      Wednesday, <locus target = "#22v"/>;
                      Thursday, <locus target = "#26v"/>;
                      Friday, <locus target = "#33v"/>;
                      Saturday, <locus target = "#37r"/>;
                      Sunday, <locus target = "#40r"/>)
                    </note>
                    </msItem>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i5"><locus from = "49r" to = "56r"/><title type = "complete" ref = "LIT2736RepCh20"/></msItem>
               </msContents>
